records.addlTxt: with Elements of criminal offenses to which plea is being entered.

10:50 AM District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Niki Kane. Defendant Dakota E Baran in court.  Attorney Jessica A Klein in court for Dakota E Baran. 

The Court conducts a plea colloquy with the Defendant.
The Defendant pleads no contest to Count 1.
The Court finds the Defendant guilty of Count 1.
The State strikes the repeater enhancer.

The State gives its sentencing recommendation.
The Defense gives its sentencing recommendation.
The Defendant presents a statement.


Court orders the following:
	
Fine:  $694.00
DNA Sample and Surcharge:  $200.00
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Payment of Fine/Forfeiture/Costs/Surcharges:  Defendant to pay $100.00 per month commencing September 15, 2022 and each month thereafter until satisfied.  Civil judgment to be entered as penalty for non payment.

HOW TO PAY:
Payments can be made on-line with a MasterCard or electronic check at:  http://wcca.wicourts.gov  (Read the agreement, then click "I agree," then click "Pay fees on-line.")  OR you may contact the Waukesha County Clerk of Courts Business Center at 262-548-7497.
Effective August 1, 2022, this case is assigned to Branch 7 Judicial Vacancy, pursuant to 22-SO-04(67).

Signed by Judge Laura Lau July 20, 2022.  Atty. Jessica Klein has been appointed.  Court orders repayment at $100.00/month with the first payment due 09/01/2022.  (BC)
**Copy of this order with cover letter mailed to the defendant 7/20/22 (am)**
Filed by the defendant. **Reviewed by Judge Lau - Petition granted. Payment plan of $100 per month, commencing September 1, 2022.**
